### Test Appointments API Endpoints
### This file can be used with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@authToken = YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Create a new appointment (POST /api/appointments)
POST {{baseUrl}}/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patient_name": "John Doe",
  "patient_email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "patient_phone": "+1234567890",
  "dentist_email": "dentist@example.com",
  "reason": "Regular checkup",
  "appointment_date": "2025-11-01",
  "appointment_time": "10:00",
  "payment_method": "cash",
  "notes": "First time patient"
}

### 2. Get appointments for a dentist (GET /api/appointments/dentist/:dentistEmail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments/dentist/dentist@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Get appointments for a dentist with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments/dentist/dentist@example.com?status=pending&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Get appointments for a patient (GET /api/appointments/patient/:email)
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments/patient/john.doe@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Get appointment by ID (GET /api/appointments/:id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments/APPOINTMENT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Update appointment (PUT /api/appointments/:id)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/appointments/APPOINTMENT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "confirmed",
  "notes": "Confirmed by dentist"
}

### 7. Cancel appointment (DELETE /api/appointments/:id)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/appointments/APPOINTMENT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
